plement Closeable, so I’m thinking of wrapping it within a Closeable DataSource. The JdbcConnectionPool does seem to implement necessary interfaces like Closeable and DataSource. I could use that, but I’m unsure about how its dynamic metadata would fit into the native context. Testing Quill with H2 is important, but there’s also the idea of creating an in-memory DataSource with mock connections, which could help with testing, but it feels complex.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking build.gradle requirements**\\n\\nI’m considering using H2, but first, I need to check if JUnit is included in the build.gradle file since that plugin provides necessary testing functionality. If I add H2, I wonder if Hikari is already included as a transitive dependency. However, without H2 present, I can’t compile anything related to org.h2, so that’s crucial. Plus, I’ll need to import Quill as well to ensure everything works together.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DxnWSsRqetZZkdlDyGAFsCMq|fc_016979b3c33f99ac0169faaabc8b08819eba854c8c9eb7e3fc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata -path '*h2*' -maxdepth 5 -type f | head -20; rg -n 'com.h2database:h2|com.h2database/h2|org.h2' metadata tests/src/com.h2database 2>/dev/null | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5216, "output": 2258, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44850, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778035357899, "responseId": "resp_016979b3c33f99ac0169faaa9e8a8c819e9e9c5b45a81bc7e0"}}
